        "scenario": "Sustained S3 outage",
        "handling": "unhandled",
        "recommendation": "No circuit breaker — during a sustained S3 outage, every request will burn through 3 attempts × 30s = 90s of server resources before failing. This will exhaust connection pools and thread/goroutine capacity, causing cascading failure. Add a circuit breaker that opens after N consecutive S3 failures and fails fast."
